arStrings.szText: "Tell me of the trophies behind you."
We display these trophies to honor the ancients, and guide their wisdom to us. The skulls remind me that death is always close at hand... theirs, or your own.
First the collective reason for displaying the trophies, then a personal reflection
(sigh) There is one skull I'm saving a place for: that of a goatman we've named Kauller the Collector. It hunts north of here, openly feasting on our fallen.
Kauller has challenged us. Were you to bring me its damned ugly head, you would gain great favor with the tribe.
